2014-01~03
http://www.bangkokpost.com/opinion/opinion/402470/we-are-obliged-to-protect-refugees

Bangkok Post
Whether fleeing Myanmar, Syria, North Korea or China’s troubled Xinjiang province, those seeking to escape persecution know that if caught the punishment might be worse. They know, too, they are relying on those operating outside the law who trade in moving people for profit, people who don’t always have their best interests at heart. It takes courage and it takes money: 100,000 baht per adult migrant, 50,000 baht for children and an extra 60,000 baht if fake passports are required.

